biogHists.text:
Jack Gould (1914-1993), journalist, worked for the New York Times from 1937 to 1972, where he covered show business, radio and television. He was married to Carmen Lewis Gould.

From the description of Gould, Jack, family papers, 1812-1993. (University of Texas Libraries). WorldCat record id: 38058254
